article.description: TJ Shorts II and Matt Neufeld each scored 17 points and UC Davis overcame a spirted fight from NAIA-member William Jessup for an 83-65 win on Sunday.
article.headline: UC Davis pulls away late from NAIA William Jessup, 83-65
article.linkText: UC Davis pulls away late from NAIA William Jessup, 83-65
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- TJ Shorts II and Matt Neufeld each scored 17 points and UC Davis overcame a spirted fight from NAIA-member William Jessup for an 83-65 win on Sunday. Garrison Goode's layup made it 13-8 in favor of UC Davis before the Warriors used a 17-4 run and led 25-17 on Tyras Rattler Jr.'s 3-pointer with 9:42 before halftime. William Jessup led 38-31 at the break and was aided by 14-of-15 shooting from the foul line and a 25-16 rebounding advantage. The Aggies regrouped after the break with a 15-4 run and led 46-42 on Neufeld's dunk with 15:01 left. Jayden DeJoseph's layup six minutes later kept William Jessup in range and the Warriors trailed 59-57. But Caleb Fuller sandwiched a 3-pointer and a layup around a layup from Shorts and UC Davis led 72-60 with 5:19 to go. Rogers Printup scored 13 for UC Davis and Fuller scored 12. Rattler led William Jessup with 14 points, Isaiah Milan, 13 and Keith Phillips and Oliver Amajoyi each scored 10.
